Goâ€™s defer keyword allows us to schedule a function to run before a function returns. Multiple functions can be deferred from a function. defer is often used to cleanup resources, finish function-scoped tasks, and similar. Deferring functions are great for maintability. By deferring, for example, we reduce the risk of forgetting to close the file in the rest of the program:</p>
